title: Wrecked Part 2 will be out Tonight or Tomorrow!
body:
(Emergency Contact) (sneak peek)

“Sometimes when I’m in a taxi I close my eyes and pretend I’m rushing somewhere fantastic in some sort of ship.” You say giggling, your words ringing out something musical, but drunk and undescribably fantastic. Jimin had nodded along rapt with the way you were talking, low and tired.

“Come on,” you tugged at his arm, “pretend with me” your hand stays intertwined with his on the middle seat of the taxi, slotting into his feeling absolutely perfect and Jimin had found himself unable to look away from you at all, unable to close his eyes for even a second. 

that one night stand turned into coffee and breakfast. Which turned into a date, and then another, and then many more before Jimin had finally made you his. Many more drunken nights, days spent in bliss in your arms, No matter how hung-over you were. you’d both grown up a little in your relationship and by the end of it, you had preferred to spend the nights sober in each other’s arms as opposed to slinking in some club just to make out in the bathroom. Jimin had barely been around enough to do just that. 

Jimin has never seen you this drunk before though- you’re barely holding yourself up. you don’t get this drunk ever or at least not often.

Over the bartender’s shoulder you spot Jimin, and surprisingly you shout, “baby!” and move to throw yourself into his arms. he catches you of course, barely managing to get his arms under yours before you fall to the ground in front of him.  

This is about as far as from what Jimin anticipated as possible. This reunion so different from the one he’d imagined in his head of meeting you by accident at a party or at a convenience store, or bumping in to you at your favorite park. maybe invite you to a coffee to catch up with him. You pull yourself out of the booth far enough almost falling forward.

 The bartender sends a scalding look Jimin’s way before he makes himself scarce and Jimin is hauling you up. Grabbing your jacket and shoving your keys and wallet into the pocket of his coat.

“Woojin” you babble against his ear, your hands linking around his neck. Of course, this is just his luck, you’re so drunk you can’t even recognize Jimin- it’s obvious that you think Jimin is your current boyfriend. jimin tells himself not to be hurt, to just appreciate having you in his arms again after so long spent apart. He swallows down the disappointment because he wishes you were that happy to see him. You talk on, not realizing that the arms around you are not that of your current boyfriends but of your ex’s. 

 “I know you’re mad at me because I said I was still in love with my Ex but I promise- I promise I’m really really gonna try to get over him this time.”
